{"session_id":"svc-1778394416107023094","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-05-10T06:26:58.13094326Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"sonnet","sticky":{"key_present":true,"bonus":0},"utilization":{"observed_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"},"requested_harness":"claude","resolved_harness":"claude","harness_source":"request_harness","requested_model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","resolved_model":"sonnet","work_dir":"/var/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-2b8170eb-20260510T062652-9884a20e","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead inside an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the completion contract — every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file you can point to after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The bead is too big when any of these holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs as separate top-level deliverables.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized sub-pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across more than ~5 files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, treat Step 0 as a split-first pass and favor child-bead scoping before implementation.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, decomposed children may split once more, and third-level splits must be rejected with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose — do not attempt the work:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child slice (focused title, description, AC; copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add \u0026lt;child-id\u0026gt; \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` to record edges.\u0026#xA;3. `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;` so the decomposition is visible.\u0026#xA;4. Write `.ddx/executions/20260510T062652-9884a20e/no_changes_rationale.txt` listing each child ID and slice, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;A clean decomposition is a successful attempt. Do not mix partial implementation with decomposition.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC against concrete evidence (test name, file path, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; conventional-commit subject ending with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `.ddx/executions/20260510T062652-9884a20e/no_changes_rationale.txt` (what is done, what blocks, what a follow-up needs) before exiting. No commit and no rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`. A well-justified no_changes beats a bad commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;`.ddx/executions/20260510T062652-9884a20e/no_changes_rationale.txt` must contain one:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;cmd\u0026gt;` — repo cwd; exit 0 closes, nonzero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: open` + `reason: \u0026lt;retryable\u0026gt;` — open, smart retry.\u0026#xA;- `status: proposed` + `reason: \u0026lt;operator needed\u0026gt;` — operator lane.\u0026#xA;- `status: blocked` + `reason: \u0026lt;external blocker\u0026gt;` — blocked lane.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;No pseudo-statuses. Bare rationales and `status: needs_investigation` reject.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Freestanding artifacts (investigation reports, findings docs) go under `.ddx/executions/20260510T062652-9884a20e/` (the per-attempt evidence directory under `.ddx/executions/`). **Never write reports to `/tmp` or any path outside the repository** — out-of-repo paths are invisible to the post-merge reviewer and cause BLOCK on missing evidence. If the bead names a specific in-repo path, use it; else default to `.ddx/executions/20260510T062652-9884a20e/\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md`. Stage and commit the report alongside code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Mode and overrides\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;DDX_MODE=bead_execution: edit code/docs for bead AC. Only broad queue-steward default is overridden; tracker, merge-policy, verification, safety stay active. Bead description/AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and project defaults.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized; running it corrupts the bead queue.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other project-instructions files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator — do not keep exploring or testing.\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-2b8170eb\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003etests: investigate exec.Command subprocesses with hardcoded /tmp paths\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM\u0026#xA;  The 2026-05-09 test-cleanup audit identified two follow-up investigations\u0026#xA;  it could not complete with read-only static analysis. Both relate to\u0026#xA;  potential /tmp leak surfaces that may or may not be real:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;    1. Tests that spawn exec.Command subprocesses passing hardcoded /tmp\u0026#xA;       paths as args (e.g. cli/cmd/agent_test.go:150 area). Static analysis\u0026#xA;       confirmed the paths are struct-literal usage; a runtime check is\u0026#xA;       needed to confirm none of those subprocesses actually write files\u0026#xA;       at those paths.\u0026#xA;    2. The testLibraryOnce race window — concurrent test packages calling\u0026#xA;       GetTestLibraryPath simultaneously from different test binaries.\u0026#xA;       This is largely subsumed by the sister bead that removes the\u0026#xA;       sync.Once shared-fixture pattern entirely, but should be verified\u0026#xA;       once that bead lands.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;CURRENT STATE\u0026#xA;  - cli/cmd/agent_test.go:150 (and similar sites) pass /tmp-rooted args to\u0026#xA;    exec.Command. Static read of the call sites suggests they\u0026#39;re\u0026#xA;    placeholders, but a dynamic test would confirm.\u0026#xA;  - The sister bead \u0026#34;tests: replace shared /tmp/.test-library fixture with\u0026#xA;    t.TempDir-scoped repo\u0026#34; addresses the architectural fix that eliminates\u0026#xA;    the race window. Verification that no race-condition leak remained\u0026#xA;    pre-fix is a separate confirmation step.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;  - Run cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./cmd/... -run \u0026#39;.*\u0026#39; under strace or fs-watcher\u0026#xA;    instrumentation (or instrument with a small exec.LookPath wrapper that\u0026#xA;    records subprocess argv) and capture every /tmp path written by a\u0026#xA;    test binary or its children.\u0026#xA;  - For each confirmed leak surface (if any), file a follow-on bead with\u0026#xA;    the specific file:line and a t.TempDir() fix.\u0026#xA;  - For the testLibraryOnce race: after the shared-fixture bead lands,\u0026#xA;    grep cli/cmd for any residual sync.Once-around-fs-state pattern;\u0026#xA;    document that none remain or file a follow-on if any are found.\u0026#xA;  - This bead\u0026#39;s deliverable is a short investigation report under\u0026#xA;    .ddx/executions/\u0026lt;run-id\u0026gt;/tmp-leak-investigation.md naming each\u0026#xA;    confirmed leak (or stating \u0026#34;no additional leaks confirmed\u0026#34;).\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;  - Fixing newly-discovered leaks (file a follow-on bead per finding).\u0026#xA;  - Investigating non-Go tests or frontend tests.\u0026#xA;  - Re-running the original static audit.\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. .ddx/executions/\u0026lt;run-id\u0026gt;/tmp-leak-investigation.md exists, listing every confirmed /tmp write surface from exec.Command subprocesses (or explicitly stating \u0026#34;no additional leaks confirmed\u0026#34;).\u0026#xA;2. The report names the instrumentation method used (strace, exec wrapper, fs-watcher, etc.) and the test packages exercised.\u0026#xA;3. Each confirmed-leak finding either has a follow-on bead filed (id captured in the report) or is fixed inline if trivial (one-liner t.TempDir() swap).\u0026#xA;4. lefthook run pre-commit passes.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003ephase:6, area:tests, kind:investigation, prevention\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata base-rev=\"dd78ba78404c0cba53b6b3fc80f78aa540eb5fc9\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260510T062652-9884a20e\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cnote\u003eNo governing references were pre-resolved. The bead description above is the primary contract. If it names files, specs, or prior beads, read those before editing. Ground decisions in what is already in the repository; do not guess.\u003c/note\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"DDX_MODE":"bead_execution","attempt_id":"20260510T062652-9884a20e","base_rev":"dd78ba78404c0cba53b6b3fc80f78aa540eb5fc9","bead_id":"ddx-2b8170eb","bundle_path":".ddx/executions/20260510T062652-9884a20e","correlation_id":"ddx-2b8170eb:20260510T062652-9884a20e","prompt_file":".ddx/executions/20260510T062652-9884a20e/prompt.md","prompt_sha":"a5411fa5fce071b54542247ca755418570afa5e9ee6221506c2c7cf52d78d5cc","role":"implementer","session_id":"eb-adc4c705","worker_id":""}}}
